OL,1,D]S737{kkkc5FBlack children over-policed
OL,2,D]S555{jjj25Fin schools, report says    
OL,3,D]Suuu{rrzq5F                           
OL,4,T#######################################
OL,5, Black children are more likely to face 
OL,6, tougher punishments at school because  
OL,7, they are viewed as "less innocent" and 
OL,8, more adult-like, a report says.        
OL,10,FThis process of "adultification" means 
OL,11,Fblack children can feel unsafe and     
OL,12,Fover-policed at school, the Commission 
OL,13,Fon Young Lives in England report says. 
OL,15,FThis can lead to black children being  
OL,16,Fdisciplined more harshly - including   
OL,17,Fbeing more likely to be excluded.      
OL,19,FThe government said it had strengthened
OL,20,Fsafeguarding guidance for schools.     
